{
  "doc_id": "59657",
  "text": "Adequate sedation is important in the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU) following UPPP to ensure patient comfort and decrease the duration of mechanical ventilation (MV), PACU stay, and bleeding [CITATION_1] . The anesthetic propofol is commonly used in the ICU for sedation of the ventilated postsurgical patient [CITATION_2] . However, propofol sedation may also cause respiratory depression, which may be accentuated by the concurrent use of opioids [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
